fields.title: Vlad the Imp Aler
fields.description: The 2017 vintage of Cascade Brewing Company's classic ale just made it to our warehouse. Supplies are limited.

fields.title: Eclipse Stouts
fields.description: We have a selection of this award-winning stout matured in various barrels.

fields.title: Fresh IPAs from Other Half
fields.description: Straight from the legendary New York Brewery, packaged less than a week ago, get them while they're fresh.

fields.title: New Beers from Fuerst Wiacek
fields.description: The rising star of the German craft beer scene is here! See what we have to offer.

fields.title: Newest Arrivals
fields.description: We've got a large selection of new products. Check them out here.

fields.name: Tropic Thunder
fields.description: Tropic Thunder is a joint effort with nomadic brewer Brian Strumke of Stillwater Artisanal. We brewed this sour ale with lactobacillus and let it ferment with plentiful Mango, Passion fruit and Peach. Sweet!

fields.name: Big Idjit
fields.description: This is a bigger and bolder version of our classic imperial stout Idjit. So, what does that make this beer then? An imperialer (it’s a word) stout? A more imperial stout? Let’s just say it’s big. Big idjit!

fields.name: FRESH
fields.description:
FRESH is all we’ve learnt during our journey towards super crisp, nicely sparkling and crushingly lush. An evolving idea of the perfect IPA that came to this. That’s fresh. This is FRESH. Gotta be fresh!

Well, it took os long enough. Still, what a ride it’s been. After no less than seventeen versions of our IPA series FRESH it has come to this; come full circle: FRESH, our new, yet very familiar, IPA. Over the different versions we’ve tried different malt bills, playing around with the pilsner malt or extra pale malt to rice ratio. We’ve tried a lot of hop combos. And, we’ve even messed around with fermentation and yeast. Now, we’re not saying that this is where it ends. There might still be versions of FRESH. However, this could be it. And, this is fresh. Because, as you know, you gotta be fresh.

fields.name: Mango Mango Mango
fields.description: It might sound like an echo, but it’s not. This collaboration with Stillwater Artisanal explores the true depth of Mango flavor. Three layers of taste and aroma from fruit and hops. Go Mango!

fields.name: Mango Mango Mango
fields.description: It might sound like an echo, but it’s not. This collaboration with Stillwater Artisanal explores the true depth of Mango flavor. Three layers of taste and aroma from fruit and hops. Go Mango!

fields.name: Black Currant
fields.description: Black Currant is a sour beer fermented with black currants. To give the beer its sour taste we add lactobacillus to the mix. A beer within the New Nordic Beer project, brewed with only Nordic ingredients.

fields.name: Tropic Thunder
fields.description: Tropic Thunder is a joint effort with nomadic brewer Brian Strumke of Stillwater Artisanal. We brewed this sour ale with lactobacillus and let it ferment with plentiful Mango, Passion fruit and Peach. Sweet!

fields.name: Fudge
fields.description: Fudge is part of a journey. A journey towards the perfect stout, towards utopia. Step by step, beer by beer, on and on. Forever! A grand canvas colored with cocoa and vanilla. For any fudgy needs.  Chewy!

fields.name: Red Layers
fields.description: Layer upon layer upon layer. Three different kinds of raspberries. Purée, juice and powder! And, a collaboration with J. Wakefield, Florida, USA, at that. This sour beer is berry berry berry heaven. Cake!

fields.name: Windmill & Airport
fields.description: A red wine barrel aged collaboration between De Molen and Dugges, two breweries that have grown up together. Dried fruits, rummy, winey, maple and heather honey sensations followed by a dry finish. Mature!

fields.name: Vlad the Imp Aler (2017)
fields.description: Behold the return of Vlad the Imp Aler, one of the most iconic projects in our 20-year history of brewing and blending sour beer. A combination of quad and blond ales aged in bourbon and wine barrels for up to two years with orange peel and coriander, Vlad delivers a fresh acidity and light malt sweetness with notes of bourbon, citrus and spice.

fields.name: Kriek (2017)
fields.description: Kriek is a blend of sour red ales aged in red wine barrels for up to 17 months with more than 16,000 pounds of fresh Bing and Sour pie cherries.

fields.name: Pêche Fumé (2017)
fields.description: Péche Fumé is a blend of wheat ales brewed with cherrywood smoked malt and aged in oak barrels for up to 14 months with Northwest-grown peaches. Delicately balancing bold elements of smoke and fruit, Péche Fumé captures notes of fresh preaches and campfire smoke with hints of dried apples and lemon zest.

fields.name: Vitis Noble (2016)
fields.description: Vitis Noble, meaning noble vine, features sour wheat and blond ales aged in oaks barrels for up to 16 months with Willamette Valley grown chardonnay grapes, one of the most celebrated "noble" varietals. This Northwest sour ale captures the vibrancy of chardonnay complemented by a kiss of French oak and notes of melon, apple and tropical fruit.

fields.name: Apricot (2019)
fields.description: Apricot is a blend of sour blond ales aged in oak wine barrels for up to 14 months, then naturally fermented with Northwest-grown apricots and aged on the fruit for an additional six months before packaging. As one of the first and longest-running blends in our portfolio, Apricot has become a quintessential part of Cascade Brewing’s identity as a producer of Northwest sour ales.

fields.name: Framblanc (2017)
fields.description: Framblanc is a blend of sour blond ales aged for up to 14 months in oak wine barrels with more than 3,500 pounds of white raspberries. Fresh aromas of raspberries, green grapes, white peaches and pears earned Framblanc the gold medal at the 2017 Oregon Beer Awards.

fields.name: Coral Horizon
fields.description: Coral Horizon is a blend of sour blond ales aged in oak wine barrels for up to 16 months with late infusions of grapefruit zest, hibiscus tea and freshly chopped ginger root. Pouring a brilliant coral-red hue reminiscent of a summer sunset, this small batch blend offers a soft, approachable acidity level with aromas of ruby red grapefruit and a refreshing ginger spice.

fields.name: Rose City Sour (2017)
fields.description: Celebrating Portland’s reputation as the City of Roses, we are pleased to offer Rose City Sour, a blend of wheat and blond ales aged in oak wine barrels for up to 14 months with rose petals, rose hips and hibiscus flowers. Rose City Sour captures the delicate floral aromas of fresh roses matched with notes of dried cranberries, pomegranates and a hint of white pepper.

fields.name: AUPA
fields.description: "Certificate of Excellence" Brussels Beer Challenge 2015. Classic Californian Pale Ale. Aromatic. Citrus.

fields.name: Coco Chango
fields.description: Imperial Porter elaborada con centeno, avena, chocolate y coco tostado.

fields.name: SSD
fields.description: San diego-style double IPA with Vic Secret and Ella hops.

fields.name: Space Jelly
fields.description: Citra only IPA

fields.name: Airhead
fields.description:
Airhead
-
Smoothie IPA with Tangerine, Kiwi, Lime & Milk Sugar – Hopped with Loral.
-
ABV: 6.0 %
OG: 16.0 P
-
Yeast: American Ale II
Contains: Water, Barley Malt, Wheat Malt, Rye Malt, Kiwi, Lime, Tangerine, Hops, Milk Sugar, Malt Extract, Yeast

fields.name: Turtledove
fields.description:
Turtledove
-
DIPA – Dry hopped with Citra & Columbus.
-
ABV: 8.0 %
OG: 18.5 P
-
Yeast: London Ale III
Contains: Water, Barley Malt, Wheat Malt, Rye Malt, Hops, Malt Extract, Dextrose, Yeast

fields.name: Sunshine & Opportunity
fields.description: Mixed fermentation saison, aged in oak barrels and dry-hopped.

fields.name: Dogpatch Currant
fields.description: Sour red ale with currants aged in wine barrels

fields.name: DDH Galaxy IPA
fields.description: Double dry-hopped New England IPA with Galaxy hops.

fields.name: Le Petit Prince
fields.description: Throughout Northern Europe, light-bodied, well-hopped, low alcohol table beers were often the beverage of choice with all meals at times and in places where the water wasn’t always safe to drink. Le Petit Prince is a dry, unspiced, highly attenuated Farmhouse Table Beer unique to our land in the Texas Hill Country. Naturally occurring wild yeasts impart a sense of place to this unfiltered, unpasteurized, 100% naturally conditioned ale.

fields.name: Das Wunderkind!
fields.description: Made using the once commonplace, Old World technique of bière de coupage, freshly hopped, young beer is blended with old, sour beer aged in oak barrels. Das Wunderkind! is dry, highly attenuated, unspiced, tart, floral, and funky. Unfiltered, unpasteurized, and 100% naturally conditioned.

fields.name: Figlet
fields.description: Collaboration with Franklin Barbecue. Farmhouse Ale refermented with smoked Texas figs.

fields.name: Bière de Miel
fields.description: On brewday, we added raw, Texas wildflower honey from Good Flow Honey Co. in Austin, Texas late in the boil. After the first several weeks of fermentation, we added more honey to the beer. Finally, the beer was 100% naturally refermented in bottles, kegs, and casks using more of the raw, Texas wildflower honey. In addition to the honey, Bière de Miel was brewed with Hill Country well water, malted barley, malted wheat, and hops. It is 5.8% alcohol by volume, 3.2 pH, has a finishing gravity of 1.003, and is suitable for vegetarians but not vegans.

fields.name: Eclipse - Salted Caramel (2019)
fields.description: Now in its 12th vintage, 2019 Eclipse is our rich Imperial Stout aged to perfection in whiskey and spirit barrels. All Eclipse starts with the same base beer bringing hints of dark chocolate, espresso, and a smooth complexity, with each barrel treatment delivering its own unique character after a minimum of 180 days of aging. Salted Caramel is brewed with caramel and aged in bourbon and salt brine barrels.

fields.name: Eclipse - Banana Fritter (2019)
fields.description: Now in its 12th vintage, 2019 Eclipse is our rich Imperial Stout aged to perfection in whiskey and spirit barrels. All Eclipse starts with the same base beer bringing hints of dark chocolate, espresso, and a smooth complexity, with each barrel treatment delivering its own unique character after a minimum of 180 days of aging. Banana Fritter is brewed with bananas, cinnamon, and sugar. Aged in rum barrels.

fields.name: Eclipse - HW (High West)  (2019)
fields.description: Now in its 12th vintage, 2019 Eclipse is our rich Imperial Stout aged to perfection in whiskey and spirit barrels. All Eclipse starts with the same base beer bringing hints of dark chocolate, espresso, and a smooth complexity, with each barrel treatment delivering its own unique character after a minimum of 180 days of aging. High West (HW) is aged in select bourbon barrels from Utah.

fields.name: Eclipse - Old Trestle (2019)
fields.description: Now in its 12th vintage, 2019 Eclipse is our rich Imperial Stout aged to perfection in whiskey and spirit barrels. All Eclipse starts with the same base beer bringing hints of dark chocolate, espresso, and a smooth complexity, with each barrel treatment delivering its own unique character after a minimum of 180 days of aging. Old Trestle® is aged exclusively in Old Trestle® bourbon barrels from Truckee, California.

fields.name: Eclipse - Barrel Cuvée (2019)
fields.description: Now in its 12th vintage, 2019 Eclipse is our rich Imperial Stout aged to perfection in whiskey and spirit barrels. All Eclipse starts with the same base beer bringing hints of dark chocolate, espresso, and a smooth complexity, with each barrel treatment delivering its own unique character after a minimum of 180 days of aging. Barrel Cuvée is our brewer's bourbon blend of our longest aged barrels.

fields.name: How Long Did It Take You To Grow That Mustache?
fields.description:
Warm, dank, heavy citrus, medium-full body, soft carb/bitterness.

Brewed  and dry hopped with Mandarina Bavaria and Hallertau Blanc

fields.name: A Nightmare On George Street
fields.description:
Bright citrus aromatics with undertones of mango and lychee. Medium bodied. Soft carbonation.

Collaboration w/ Equilibrium Brewery

fields.name: Therapeutic Tepache
fields.description: Fruited Sour brewed with piloncillo sugar & grains of paradise and with cinnamon, ginger, habanero and pineapple purée added

fields.name: ITS SO QUIET AND PEACEFUL WALKING ACROSS THE BROOKLYN BRIDGE
fields.description: DDH Pale Ale. Hops: Mosaic. Ample notes of pulpy orange, evergreen, blueberries and subtle pine. Light-medium bodied. Creamy mouthfeel. Soft bitterness.

fields.name: ET Found Home
fields.description: Bright floral aromatics with light notes of honey and bready malt, creamy mouthfeel with smooth bitterness.

fields.name: THESE DRINKS ARE SO EXPENSIVE. DO I HAVE TO TIP?
fields.description: DDH IPA. Hops: Citra, Citra Cryo and Wai-iti. Mango, pineapple, passion fruit and orange. Light-medium body. Creamy mouthfeel. 6.5% ABV

fields.name: I Don't Feel Like Taking the Subway. Let's Take A Cab All the Way There.
fields.description: DDH DIPA (hops: citra, ekuanot, ekuanot cryo). Mango, passionfruit, lime and berry notes. Medium bodied. Creamy mouthfeel. Subtle bitterness.

fields.name: Oro Negro
fields.description: Oil of Aphrodite brewed with walnuts and conditioned on spices

fields.name: The Ties That Bind
fields.description: American Wild Ale

fields.name: Quatrefoil
fields.description: A blend of 1 to 3-year-old oak aged sour blond ale conditioned upon apricots. There is no mistaking the dried apricot dynamic of sour and sweet. The apricots and the aged sour blond ale add a lovely stone fruit presence that resonates through the entire experience.

fields.name: Bourbon Barrel Dark Apparition
fields.description: Russian Imperial Stout aged in bourbon barrels for a year

fields.name: Jelly King
fields.description:
An everyday, juicy, drinkable sour with punchy hop aromatics and fruity foundational
flavours. Low bitterness, light body, and pale yellow in colour, with notes of fuzzy peach,
tangerine, and cedar.

fields.name: Let There Be Silence (Barrel Aged Quad)
fields.description: Inspired by the gift of empty whiskey barrels used in the first run of Tennessee Rye Whiskey by our friends at Pennington Distilling Co. in Nashville, Tennessee, we set out to raft a beer that would complement this stories batch. The result is a Belgian-style dark ale aged six months in barrel with native flora. A garnet-hued quadruple with aromas of molasses, leather, cocoa, tobacco and port accompanied by hints of toffee, oak, tart dried fruit, and spice on the palate. With bright effervescence, it is spritely on the palate with gentle acidity and a soft, spicy, drying finish.

fields.name: Abbey Tripel
fields.description: A light golden Belgian inspired Abbey-style Tripel

fields.name: Bam Di Castagna
fields.description: A fall inspired version of Bam Biére. Brewed with chestnuts in the mash, Bam de Castsagna pours a rich auburn and is gently tart. Notes of earthy chestnuts, flavors of cashew, taro with traces of autumn smoke.

fields.name: Lucky Cat
fields.description: Perhaps this cool cat beckoned you from a shelf or a cooler. Well, lucky you! You’re holding a Pipeworks Lucky Cat is brewed with Mosaic Hops and hibiscus with strawberries added. MeWoWie! We’re not claiming that this cat will bring you good fortune, perfect health, beauty, or even ultimate happiness, but it will bring you deliciousness! So wave your paw if you’d like to welcome this brew into your glass, and then explain to anyone around you why you’re waving your paw (especially if you read this silently to yourself).

fields.name: Dot Ave
fields.description: Beginning at Milton Lower Mills and spanning all the way to the Fort Point Channel, Dorchester Avenue dates back to 1805 and is rich with history. It's also the namesake of our Nelson Sauvin dry-hopped addition to the Avenue Series. Presenting a glowing deep yellow, Dot Ave offers an aroma with layers of depth and nuance. Immediately apparent is the tropical shade of the Nelson variety, with notes of mango and pineapple jumping from the glass. As the beer warms, underlying notes of concord grape, lemon verbena, and earthy pine make an appearance. Soft, palate-coating, and highly drinkable, Dot Ave finishes balanced and evolves throughout each sip.

fields.name: Vicinity
fields.description: Originally brewed in celebration of the first anniversary of Row 34, our favorite Fort Point oyster bar and craft-beer purveyor, Vicinity highlights a neighborhood collaboration of passion and vision. The beer's appearance is a yellow straw-color, with a significant haze. Heavy citrus aromas of pineapple, orange flesh and mango dance on the nose and palate. The pilsner malt provides a medium body and wraps up each sip with a slight balancing bitterness.

fields.name: Double Dry Hopped Fort Point
fields.description: This double dry hopped pale ale contains the same base ingredients, for both malt and hops, as Fort Point Pale Ale, but with an additional dry hop of Citra. The added hops richly enhance the juicy tropical fruit flavors of pineapple/mango, create elevated green, herbaceous aromatics, and increase body.

fields.name: Double Dry Hopped Small Green Everything
fields.description: Double Dry Hopped Small Green Everything is a Session IPA hopped with a disproportionate amount of Motueka, Amarillo, Citra and Mosaic for it’s size. It then receives a second dry hop addition of Mosaic and Citra Lupulin powder.

fields.name: Double Dry Hopped Small Galaxy Everything
fields.description: Kind of hard to believe we've never made a Galaxy version of this beer. Problem corrected.

fields.name: Triple Cream
fields.description: Triple Cream is a Triple Dry Hopped Imperial Oat Cream IPA. It's an even bigger version of Cheddar Imperial IPA brewed with lactose and tons of oats! We then hopped it with Wai-iti, Kohatu, Ekuanot, and Citra. This was followed by a triple dry hopping, including an all Galaxy hop final dry hop and tons of Citra lupulin powder in the second dry hop.

fields.name: Dugges Bryggeri
fields.description:
We are Dugges Bryggeri.
We love making beer.

fields.name: Other Half Brewing Co.
fields.description:
In 2014, Sam Richardson, Matt Monahan and Andrew Burman founded Other Half Brewing Company, a local brewery in New York City with a simple mission: to create beers that they wanted to drink from a company that they wanted to be a part of.

Their vision was to build a passionate team that brewed great beers in the state of New York—done so with effort and thoughtfulness—to represent the “Other Half” of the industry.

Today, Other Half craft beers in their Brooklyn brewery and are dedicated to collaborating with breweries both in New York as well as across the world in an effort to constantly move the industry forward while elevating the craft.

The Other Half team believes that local breweries play an important role in their communities which is why they partner with these other likeminded brewers and brands in local nabes across the country and the world—but always return to their home state of New York and their Brooklyn taproom.

fields.name: Cascade Brewing
fields.description: Cascade Brewing has been a pioneer in the sour beer renaissance since 2006 and is the proud innovator of the Northwest Sour Ale. Its distinctive sour beer blends feature fruit forward, barrel-aged ales with an emphasis on project year-to-year variation. These beers offer a complex array of flavors derived from the acid, the fruit and the residual flavors present in the barrels in which they age. The resulting beers offer a complex array of flavors and aromas derived from with each project year release capturing the unique subtleties of that year’s growing season. Cascade Brewing’s sour ales are brewed and blended in Portland, Oregon. They are available on draft and in 500ml bottles at its two Portland pubs, and through worldwide distribution.

fields.name: Basqueland Brewing
fields.description: Award-winning brewery located in Hernani, just outside of San Sebastian, Basque Country.

fields.name: Brasserie Cantillon
fields.description:
Brasserie Cantillon Brewery is a small and local family brewery in the city of Anderlecht in Brussels, Belgium. Founded in 1900 by Paul Cantillon, the brewery immediately became popular for its lambic beers. Some of its remarkable lambic beers are the Cantillon Kriek, Gauze and Faro. The brewery depends on raw wheat, malted barley and dried hops.

Brasserie Cantillon Brewery takes pride in its long tradition of using organic ingredients of grown cereals that promote fine quality of beers and clean agricultural practice. Spontaneous fermentation is a trademark of lambic beers produced by the brewery. Brasserie Cantillon Brewery also delivers fruit-flavored beers from oaks and wide variety of fruits.

fields.name: FUERST WIACEK
fields.description: We are a Berlin based gypsy brewer duo: Georg and Lukasz. Before going our own path, we travelled the world to learn more about brewing from some of the best breweries out there. We draw inspiration from our favorite New England and German brewing styles and mix that with our experience from apprenticing at Põhjala, Beavertown and Boneyard Beer.

fields.name: Almanac Beer Company
fields.description: Our motto, "Farm-to-Barrel", means brewing beers inspired by the great brewing traditions of the world with the best in locally sourced ingredients. Almanac Beer Company was founded in 2010 by Jesse Friedman and Damian Fagan.

fields.name: Ārpus Brewing Co.
fields.description:
Ārpus Brewing Co. is an independent microbrewery, founded in 2017 by craft beer geeks from Latvia.

We chose Latvian word Ārpus for the name of our brewery, as its meaning reflects the types of beers we brew - outside of the box, beyond the mass made light/dark lagers, beers with overwhelming flavours and aromas for people brave enough to step out of their comfort zone.

fields.name: Jester King Brewery
fields.description: Located in the beautiful Texas Hill Country, Jester King Craft Brewery is an authentic farmhouse brewery committed to brewing artisan ales of great depth and character. At times drawing influences from the world beyond traditional brewers’ yeast, Jester King’s beer is not rushed to market but allowed to mature – often in oak barrels – to create the most enjoyable, interesting and exciting beer we can make. An additional layer of complexity is added to Jester King’s bottled beers by allowing a second fermentation to take place in the bottle. As part of its commitment to sustainability, the slow food movement and Texas, Jester King beer uses as many organic and local ingredients as possible and will soon be brewed with harvested rainwater.

fields.name: FiftyFifty Brewing Co.
fields.description: Founded in 2007 in Truckee, California, FiftyFifty Brewing Co. makes world class beer for anyone living their big life. FiftyFifty is an authentic mountain town brewery and pub that pushes the boundaries to create award-winning beers. We continue to surprise experts, aficionados and ourselves with innovative new offerings for our global and local customers.  At FiftyFifty we believe everyone deserves a beer to celebrate their version of a big life.

fields.name: Evil Twin Brewing NYC
fields.description: We make exquisite craft beers for crispy beer geeks, tasty gourmands and you. We are so much in love with good taste, all the beers from Evil Twin Brewing NYC are prepared at our first brick and mortar brewery in Ridgewood, Queens, NYC. Exclusively hand picked to please you with delicate, funky, extreme and by all means rare flavors. Maybe not the easiest way, but certainly the most fun!!! A clever man once said: 'Stay thirsty... stay foolish.' That sounds like our vision, just with a tad less attitude.

fields.name: Jackie O's Brewery
fields.description:
Established in 2005, Jackie O’s Brewery has evolved over the years to include an experimental Brewpub, Public House Restaurant, Production Brewery & Taproom, Bake Shop and the Barrel Ridge Farm – all of which are located in Athens, Ohio / Southeastern, Ohio.

Jackie O's specializes in brewing techniques that revive traditional methods and also incorporate contemporary elements and influences. We strive to brew one of the most diverse beer portfolios in the country, with a detailed and unique focus on barrel & wood aged beers, wild ales, and blending.

fields.name: Bellwoods Brewery
fields.description: A Toronto brewery, pub and bottle shop located at 124 and 126 Ossington Ave., and a brewery, tasting room and bottle shop at 20 Hafis Rd.

fields.name: Trillium Brewing Company
fields.description:
Trillium Brewing was founded in March of 2013 by JC and Esther Tetreault with the desire to create a New England Farmhouse-inspired experience through the lens of craft beer. Launched with three employees and the support of family, friends, and community, our little brewery located at 369 Congress Street in Boston’s then-sleepy Fort Point neighborhood has grown to a team of nearly 300. Every member of our organization has incredible drive and purpose, working passionately each day to elevate the quality of the Trillium experience.

Beer is at the center of everything we do, and a few core values have always driven the approach to our portfolio: the desire to continue pushing boundaries of experimentation with education, keeping a focus on hospitality by attempting to offer a wide range of styles for a diverse audience, and keeping our team excited and always-learning. With hundreds of unique offerings available each year, we take pride in the diversity and breadth of beer that we produce.

With two year-round locations in the Fort Point and Fenway neighborhoods, as well as a seasonal beer garden on the Rose Kennedy Greenway, Boston is the heart of our operations. Our production brewery and taproom in Canton and our soon-to-be operational farm in North Stonington, Connecticut round out our five current locations. In the coming years, visitors to Canton will enjoy our ‘forever home’, Located minutes from the current location, and will include a larger taproom and brewery.

fields.name: Blackberry Farm Brewery
fields.description: At the Blackberry Farm Brewery, our aim is to craft beers that are unique and rooted in tradition, while speaking to natural nuances of the farm. As a small brewery, we work tirelessly to produce as much as we can, but still are maintaining a very small quantity of beers.

fields.name: Jolly Pumpkin Artisan Ales
fields.description: Every step of the process at Jolly Pumpkin Artisan Ales is carefully considered to bring about the most complex and refined beers imaginable. As a result of our dedication, most of our beers will continue to mature and mellow for quite some time when cellared at home. Enjoyment for today, and for tomorrow!

fields.name: Pipeworks Brewing Company
fields.description:
Pipeworks began, as many breweries do, in the stove top kettles and plastic-bucket fermenters of the home brewer. Beejay Oslon and Gerrit Lewis met while working at Chicago's famous West Lakeview Liquors, a haven for beer geeks in search of new and exciting brews from around the world. While working there, the two got to thinking it was time to turn their passion in to a business.

The first steps in that long journey took them to a the small town of Lo in the Belgian countryside. It was there that the Pipeworks boys lived and worked with Urbain Coutteau owner and brewer at the De Struise Brewery. While working there the boys honed their craft, learned the ins and outs of running a brewery, and had the opportunity to create their first commercially available beers. The success of these brews fueled their passion and prepared them for the work ahead of them.

Upon coming back to the States the two began experimenting with pilot batches, formulating a business plan, and developing an image for Pipeworks.

Now we are ready to bring what we've learned to the craft beer world!
